Required config entries for chef-server.sh

* chef_server_url - full URL to chef-server API endpoint (example: https://api.opscode.com/organizations/<your org>)
* validation_client_name - name of the chef-server 'validator' client for your org (example: <your org>-validator)
* chef_environment - name of the chef environment to register node (example: test_env)
* http_proxy - Specify the proxy server for chef-client HTTP traffic (example: http://proxy.example.org:3128)
* https_proxy - Specify the proxy server for chef-client HTTPS traffic (example: http://proxy.example.org:3128)
* http_proxy_user - If the proxy server requires a username, provide it here
* http_proxy_pass - If the proxy server requires a password, provide it here
* chef_validation_pem - Name of the validation pem file used to register with chef-server, this file MUST EXIST in media/chef_validators
